<h2>
    Top 10 Brown Trout Fishing Spots near Salem, Oregon
</h2>
<h3>
    1. North Santiam River
</h3>
<p>
    One of Oregon’s most famous trout streams, the <strong>North Santiam River</strong> offers deep runs, riffles, and pools perfect for brown trout. Focus on the sections near Mehama and Packsaddle Park, where cooler tributaries enter the main flow.
</p>
<h3>
    2. Detroit Lake
</h3>
<p>
    This large reservoir east of Salem is home to impressive brown trout that can exceed 20 inches. Troll spoons or plugs near the upper arms in spring and fall for the best results.
</p>
<h3>
    3. Breitenbush River
</h3>
<p>
    Flowing from the Cascade Mountains, the <strong>Breitenbush River</strong> is a pristine, cold-water paradise. Light fly setups with dry flies or nymphs work beautifully here.
</p>
<h3>
    4. Big Cliff Reservoir
</h3>
<p>
    Located below Detroit Dam, this smaller reservoir holds a mix of brown and rainbow trout. Early morning or evening trolling produces consistent bites.
</p>
<h3>
    5. Silver Creek Reservoir (Silverton)
</h3>
<p>
    Perfect for beginners and families, this lake is stocked regularly and offers easy shoreline access. Try spinners or bait rigs near the dam.
</p>
<h3>
